# ORICALO AI Agent Rules (.antigravity)

## Project Overview
ORICALO is an Urdu-first AI voice agent for real estate. It uses a monorepo
structure with Next.js (frontend) and FastAPI (backend).

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Lucide React.
- **Backend**: Python 3.10+, FastAPI, WebSockets, PyTorch, HuggingFace Transformers.
- **AI/ML**: Whisper (STT), Llama/Mistral (LLM), FAISS (RAG).

## Directory Structure
- `frontend/`: Next.js application.
- `backend/`: Python AI server.
  - `app/`: FastAPI core.
  - `stt/`: Speech-to-Text module.
  - `llm/`: LLM & Dialogue Policy.
  - `rag/`: Retrieval-Augmented Generation.
  - `tts/`: Text-to-Speech.
- `training/`: Model fine-tuning scripts.
- `models/`: Local model artifacts (ignored by Git).

## Coding Standards

### Python (Backend)
- Follow **PEP 8**.
- Use type hints (`typing.List`, `typing.Optional`, etc.).
- Use `pydantic` for data validation.
- Docstrings for public functions/classes.
- Prefer `async def` for I/O-bound operations.

### TypeScript/React (Frontend)
- Use functional components.
- Use `interface` for props.
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling.
- Use `lucide-react` for icons.
- Avoid `any` where possible.

## Agentic Behaviors
- **Plan First**: For non-trivial changes, draft an implementation plan.
- **Atomic Changes**: Keep edits focused; avoid mixing unrelated refactors.
- **Verify**: Ensure code builds/tests run after changes.
- **Urdu Support**: Keep Urdu text and RTL considerations in mind where relevant.

## Repo Hygiene & Safety
- Do **not** commit `.venv/`, `venv/`, `frontend/node_modules/`, `models/`,
  or large audio datasets under `data/test_audio/gold_set/` or
  `data/test_audio/telephony_8k/`.
- Use `.env` files for secrets; never hardcode API keys.
- Respect iteration boundaries: keep Iteration 1 cleanup, Iteration 2 features,
  and later work in separate branches/PRs.
